The paper is about object detection using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The focus of the paper is on designing an efficient network architecture for edge and mobile scenarios, which involves optimization of both computational and memory requirements, and this is a common research topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of machine-driven design exploration, which suggests the involvement of neural architecture search (NAS) techniques, a subfield of both machine learning and artificial intelligence. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed network on an embedded module, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and may involve hardware optimization.
